In the JIRA 6.1 "What's New" dialog box, two of the three items displayed are administrative changes, rather than end-user changes.

The audience for the "What's New" dialog is end-users of the JIRA instance, not the administrators.  Including administrative items in this dialog box makes it useless for the end-users.

Please either set a better policy for what is chosen for the "What's New" dialog, or add a configuration option to allow administrators to alter the content of the dialog.

